[x] read apply_sync's write ordering/locking before touching action-mirror sync $Prerequisite for the action-mirror VTODO swap (learn to import VTODO). apply_sync's doc comment says ordering is load-bearing - TakeAction/TakeCalendar/Converged each stage .actions + sidecar writes differently via PendingBatch. Need to actually trace this before changing what read_ics_dates reads, since a mis-sequenced change here can silently clear a real scheduled_at (mistaking 'can't find the old format' for 'calendar deleted the event'). See caldav-integration/README.md design notes 2026-07-12.$ %2026-07-13T22:48 #019f5a22-7252-7c22-8e66-96aae8692720
[x] decouple sync state from the domain model $The merge base B is a property of the sync pair, not the action. Move it to a sync-owned gitignored store (.clearhead/sync/<pair>.json, action-uuid -> field -> value): plan_sync takes a base_map param symmetric with ics_dates; scheduled_at_sync/due_date_sync come OFF Action and ActionMeta (merge_action/hydrate_actions_map shrink); apply_sync stamps B into the store; one-time seed migration reads existing sidecar _sync values in. Lands BEFORE the action-mirror VTODO swap. See README design notes 2026-07-14.$ !1 %2026-07-17T23:24 #019f5f76-c52c-7020-8dbc-c0f393cf196e
[x] align sync state with the configured plans vdir $Correct the initial decoupling: vdir is the integration boundary. Replace per-pair/caldav state with one clean merge-base store for the configured plan path; remove pair/remote/CalDAV concepts and delete all legacy sidecar migration code. Missing state gets first-sync semantics.$ !1 %2026-07-17T23:45 #019f73f2-7229-7362-83f1-a095084c1761
[x] learn to export things to VTODO format $Plans already emit VTODO+RRULE. Finish the standalone Action half by replacing action_to_vevent with action_to_vtodo. RRULE remains exclusively Plan semantics and never returns to the .actions DSL; recurring capture should write a Plan VTODO directly, then expansion materializes executable Action instances.$ %2026-07-23T00:03 #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3a974ca12f85
[x] learn to import VTODO $Action-mirror VTODO swap: action_to_vevent -> action_to_vtodo; Action.id is the VTODO UID and vdir filename, with no sidecar identity map. Map STATUS (blocked -> NEEDS-ACTION plus X-CLEARHEAD-STATUS:blocked), title, description, dates, priority, contexts, and completion. VTODO with RRULE is always a Plan; VTODO without RRULE is an Action projection.$ %2026-07-23T17:17 #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3abe216ea948
[x] add fields to the sync store ~ $Genericize reconcile() to reconcile<T: PartialEq + Clone> and run it independently for state, title, description, and due_date. Each merge base lives in the one configured-plans-vdir projection store, never Action/ActionMeta. One field conflict must not block the others.$ %2026-07-23T17:17 #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3adcba9847ba
[x] state %2026-07-23T17:17 #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3afc680d10bc
[x] due date %2026-07-23T17:17 #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3b1aef80a19a
[x] title %2026-07-23T17:17 #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3b3d3dbdfcce
[x] description %2026-07-23T17:17 #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3b5faede09e7
[x] migrate existing plan .ics files from VEVENT\+RRULE to VTODO\+RRULE $One-time conversion command, not a permanent dual-format read path. Run once after plan_to_event/parse_ics_file switch to VTODO; old VEVENT plan format is retired after conversion. See caldav-integration/README.md design notes 2026-07-12.$ %2026-07-23T18:51 #019f59c4-8c0b-7aa1-88b8-8ec35dee0e2d
[x] make Action UUID the VTODO identity $For ClearHead-authored standalone actions use Action.id == VTODO UID == canonical vdir filename. For calendar-authored arbitrary text UIDs, retain UID and derive Action.id deterministically with UUIDv5; remember UID only in the plans projection store so missing resources can be recreated. No charter-sidecar mirror map. Audit source_vevent/external_schedule_id so recurrence-series metadata remains only where semantically real.$ !1 %2026-07-23T18:51 #019f7455-fde8-7112-a9cc-2955902ae771
[x] import calendar-created VTODOs as actions $Create an Action in the charter selected by the VTODO resource's vdir directory. UUID UIDs remain the Action UUID; arbitrary RFC 5545 UIDs derive a deterministic UUIDv5 without rewriting UID or using a sidecar identity map. Existing Actions whose projection disappears recreate the VTODO; deletion has no lifecycle meaning.$ !1 %2026-07-23T18:51 #019f91bc-d4d8-7293-943d-ddb59f28ab84
[x] sync VTODO priority and categories bidirectionally $Map standard RFC 5545 PRIORITY and CATEGORIES independently through the same per-field three-way merge. STATUS remains the only lifecycle signal; predecessor, sequential, and charter hierarchy remain ClearHead-only.$ !2 %2026-07-23T18:51 #019f91bc-d4e7-75a2-a112-1be069c3b014
[x] align VTODO specifications and interoperability coverage $Replace stale VEVENT-authoring terminology across specs/help/comments, document import and missing-projection semantics, and cover arbitrary UIDs, transport filenames, standard fields, and unknown-property preservation.$ !2 %2026-07-23T18:51 #019f91bc-d4f1-7281-8951-bbf3c1cb6c42
[_] extract calendar sync into its own crate $Deliberately deferred after VTODO sync stabilized: the vdir projection remains cohesive inside clearhead-core and extraction would currently move code without reducing coupling. Reconsider only when a second consumer needs the boundary; any future crate must remain server-agnostic.$ %2026-07-23T18:51 #019f5f76-f52a-7251-bd29-28117bf16f47
[x] build VTODO integration ~ !1 %2026-07-23T18:51 #019f5847-e4ef-75f2-a736-831b6a828f63
